04/04/2003
STRASBOURG, France -- In a speech before the Council of Europe on Thursday (3 April), Bulgarian Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg defended his country's position on Iraq, saying it was based on the principle of human rights protection. He expressed regret over failed attempts to resolve the problem peacefully, adding that the international community should now concentrate on the reconstruction of post-war Iraq and establishing democracy. (Dnevnik, Trud, 24 Chassa - 04/04/03; BTA, Council of Europe press release - 03/04/03)
